# Plan: Add `@ai-sdk/pixel-art` Provider Package

## Context

The user wants a new fictional "PixelArt" AI provider added to the Vercel AI SDK monorepo. It should only support image generation (no text, no embeddings, no speech), export a `createPixelArt` factory function, support image settings for size, style (`"pixel"`, `"retro"`, `"8bit"`), and pixel density, and use `https://api.pixelart.ai/v1` as the base URL. The structure must mirror how existing providers (especially `@ai-sdk/fal`) are built.

No existing provider packages are to be modified — only new files are created.

---

## Reference Files (Read-Only)

| Purpose | Path |
|---|---|
| Provider factory pattern | `packages/fal/src/fal-provider.ts` |
| Image model implementation | `packages/fal/src/fal-image-model.ts` |
| Options schema pattern | `packages/fal/src/fal-image-options.ts` |
| Model ID / settings types | `packages/fal/src/fal-image-settings.ts` |
| Main exports | `packages/fal/src/index.ts` |
| Version constant | `packages/fal/src/version.ts` |
| package.json | `packages/fal/package.json` |
| tsconfig.json | `packages/fal/tsconfig.json` |
| tsconfig.build.json | `packages/fal/tsconfig.build.json` |
| tsup.config.ts | `packages/fal/tsup.config.ts` |
| vitest node config | `packages/fal/vitest.node.config.js` |
| vitest edge config | `packages/fal/vitest.edge.config.js` |
| Image model tests | `packages/fal/src/fal-image-model.test.ts` |
| Provider factory tests | `packages/fal/src/fal-provider.test.ts` |
| `ImageModelV3` interface | `packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3.ts` |
| `ProviderV3` interface | `packages/provider/src/provider/v3/provider-v3.ts` |
| Example usage | `examples/ai-functions/src/generate-image/fal/basic.ts` |

### Key utilities from `@ai-sdk/provider-utils` to reuse

- `postJsonToApi()` — POST JSON with error handling
- `getFromApi()` — GET binary data (image download)
- `createJsonResponseHandler()` — validate JSON responses with Zod
- `createJsonErrorResponseHandler()` — standard error handler
- `createStatusCodeErrorResponseHandler()` — for binary download errors
- `createBinaryResponseHandler()` — for raw image byte downloads
- `combineHeaders()` — merge header objects
- `withoutTrailingSlash()` — URL normalization
- `withUserAgentSuffix()` — add SDK version to User-Agent
- `parseProviderOptions()` — parse & validate provider-specific options
- `lazySchema()` / `zodSchema()` / `InferSchema` — schema utilities
- `loadApiKey()` — load API key from env with proper errors
- `resolve()` — resolve `Resolvable<T>` types
- `FetchFunction`, `Resolvable` — shared types

---

## Files to Create

### 1. `packages/pixel-art/package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "@ai-sdk/pixel-art",
  "version": "0.0.0",
  "license": "Apache-2.0",
  "sideEffects": false,
  "main": "./dist/index.js",
  "module": "./dist/index.mjs",
  "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
  "files": [
    "dist/**/*",
    "src",
    "!src/**/*.test.ts",
    "!src/**/*.test-d.ts",
    "!src/**/__snapshots__",
    "!src/**/__fixtures__",
    "CHANGELOG.md",
    "README.md"
  ],
  "scripts": {
    "build": "pnpm clean && tsup --tsconfig tsconfig.build.json",
    "build:watch": "pnpm clean && tsup --watch",
    "clean": "del-cli dist *.tsbuildinfo",
    "type-check": "tsc --build",
    "test": "pnpm test:node && pnpm test:edge",
    "test:update": "pnpm test:node -u",
    "test:watch": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js",
    "test:edge": "vitest --config vitest.edge.config.js --run",
    "test:node": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js --run"
  },
  "exports": {
    "./package.json": "./package.json",
    ".": {
      "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/index.js"
    }
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/provider": "workspace:*",
    "@ai-sdk/provider-utils": "workspace:*"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/test-server": "workspace:*",
    "@types/node": "20.17.24",
    "@vercel/ai-tsconfig": "workspace:*",
    "tsup": "^8",
    "typescript": "5.8.3",
    "zod": "3.25.76"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "zod": "^3.25.76 || ^4.1.8"
  },
  "engines": {
    "node": ">=18"
  },
  "publishConfig": {
    "access": "public"
  },
  "homepage": "https://ai-sdk.dev/docs",
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "git+https://github.com/vercel/ai.git"
  },
  "bugs": {
    "url": "https://github.com/vercel/ai/issues"
  },
  "keywords": ["ai"]
}
```

---

### 2. `packages/pixel-art/tsconfig.json`

```json
{
  "extends": "./node_modules/@vercel/ai-tsconfig/ts-library.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": true,
    "rootDir": "src",
    "outDir": "dist"
  },
  "exclude": ["dist", "build", "node_modules", "tsup.config.ts"],
  "references": [
    { "path": "../provider" },
    { "path": "../provider-utils" }
  ]
}
```

---

### 3. `packages/pixel-art/tsconfig.build.json`

```json
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": false
  }
}
```

---

### 4. `packages/pixel-art/tsup.config.ts`

```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'tsup';

export default defineConfig([
  {
    entry: ['src/index.ts'],
    format: ['cjs', 'esm'],
    dts: true,
    sourcemap: true,
    define: {
      __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(
        (await import('./package.json', { with: { type: 'json' } })).default
          .version,
      ),
    },
  },
]);
```

---

### 5. `packages/pixel-art/vitest.node.config.js`

```js
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import packageJson from './package.json';

export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    environment: 'node',
    include: ['**/*.test.ts', '**/*.test.tsx'],
  },
  define: {
    __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(packageJson.version),
  },
});
```

---

### 6. `packages/pixel-art/vitest.edge.config.js`

```js
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import packageJson from './package.json';

export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    environment: 'edge-runtime',
    include: ['**/*.test.ts', '**/*.test.tsx'],
  },
  define: {
    __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(packageJson.version),
  },
});
```

---

### 7. `packages/pixel-art/src/version.ts`

```ts
declare const __PACKAGE_VERSION__: string | undefined;
export const VERSION: string =
  typeof __PACKAGE_VERSION__ !== 'undefined'
    ? __PACKAGE_VERSION__
    : '0.0.0-test';
```

---

### 8. `packages/pixel-art/src/pixel-art-image-settings.ts`

Defines the model ID union type. Three fictional model tiers:

```ts
export type PixelArtImageModelId =
  | 'pixelart-v1'
  | 'pixelart-v2'
  | 'pixelart-v2-hd'
  | (string & {});
```

---

### 9. `packages/pixel-art/src/pixel-art-image-options.ts`

Zod schema for provider-specific image options passed via `providerOptions.pixelArt`:

- `style?: 'pixel' | 'retro' | '8bit'` — the art style preset
- `pixelDensity?: number` (1–64) — controls the pixelation grain
- `outputFormat?: 'png' | 'gif'` — image format

Uses `lazySchema` + `zodSchema` + `InferSchema` pattern from `@ai-sdk/provider-utils`.

```ts
import { InferSchema, lazySchema, zodSchema } from '@ai-sdk/provider-utils';
import { z } from 'zod/v4';

export const pixelArtImageModelOptionsSchema = lazySchema(() =>
  zodSchema(
    z
      .object({
        style: z.enum(['pixel', 'retro', '8bit']).nullish(),
        pixelDensity: z.number().min(1).max(64).nullish(),
        outputFormat: z.enum(['png', 'gif']).nullish(),
      })
      .passthrough(),
  ),
);

export type PixelArtImageModelOptions = InferSchema<
  typeof pixelArtImageModelOptionsSchema
>;
```

---

### 10. `packages/pixel-art/src/pixel-art-image-model.ts`

Core image generation class. Implements `ImageModelV3`.

**Internal config interface:**
```ts
interface PixelArtImageModelConfig {
  provider: string;
  baseURL: string;
  headers?: Resolvable<Record<string, string | undefined>>;
  fetch?: FetchFunction;
  _internal?: { currentDate?: () => Date };
}
```

**Class shape:**
```ts
export class PixelArtImageModel implements ImageModelV3 {
  readonly specificationVersion = 'v3';
  readonly maxImagesPerCall = 4;

  get provider(): string { return this.config.provider; }

  constructor(
    readonly modelId: PixelArtImageModelId,
    private readonly config: PixelArtImageModelConfig,
  ) {}
```

**`getArgs()` — build request body:**
- Parse `size` → `{ width, height }` by splitting on `'x'`
- If only `aspectRatio` is given, warn it is unsupported (PixelArt API requires explicit dimensions) and emit an `'unsupported'` warning
- Parse `providerOptions.pixelArt` using `parseProviderOptions()` with `pixelArtImageModelOptionsSchema`
- Build `requestBody`:
  ```json
  {
    "model": "<modelId>",
    "prompt": "...",
    "n": 1,
    "width": 512,
    "height": 512,
    "seed": 42,
    "style": "pixel",
    "pixel_density": 16,
    "output_format": "png"
  }
  ```
- Map camelCase options → snake_case API fields: `pixelDensity → pixel_density`, `outputFormat → output_format`

**`doGenerate()` — make API call and return images:**
- POST to `${baseURL}/images/generate` using `postJsonToApi()`
- Use `combineHeaders()` + `resolve()` for headers
- Validate response with Zod schema (see below)
- Download each image URL using `getFromApi()` with `createBinaryResponseHandler()`
- Return `{ images: Uint8Array[], warnings, response: { timestamp, modelId, headers }, providerMetadata }`

**Response Zod schema** for `https://api.pixelart.ai/v1/images/generate`:
```ts
const pixelArtImageSchema = z.object({
  url: z.string(),
  width: z.number().nullish(),
  height: z.number().nullish(),
});

const pixelArtResponseSchema = z.object({
  images: z.array(pixelArtImageSchema),
  model: z.string().nullish(),
  seed: z.number().nullish(),
});
```

**Error schema** for failed responses:
```ts
const pixelArtErrorSchema = z.object({
  error: z.object({
    message: z.string(),
    code: z.string().nullish(),
  }),
});
```
Use `createJsonErrorResponseHandler()` with `errorToMessage: e => e.error.message`.

**`providerMetadata`** key: `'pixelArt'` (camelCase provider name), containing `images` array and seed.

---

### 11. `packages/pixel-art/src/pixel-art-provider.ts`

```ts
export interface PixelArtProviderSettings {
  apiKey?: string;        // default: PIXELART_API_KEY env var
  baseURL?: string;       // default: 'https://api.pixelart.ai/v1'
  headers?: Record<string, string>;
  fetch?: FetchFunction;
}

export interface PixelArtProvider extends ProviderV3 {
