## Summary: Key Architectural Patterns

| Pattern | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Provider extends ProviderV3** | Standardized interface all providers implement |
| **Factory function createXXX()** | Initializes provider with settings (API key, baseURL, headers) |
| **Model factory methods** | Return model instances (createImageModel, createChatModel, etc.) |
| **Settings interface** | Configuration options (apiKey, baseURL, custom fetch, headers) |
| **Model class implements ImageModelV3** | Core implementation of image generation |
| **doGenerate() method** | Single async method handling all image generation logic |
| **Provider-specific metadata** | Response includes providerMetadata for provider-specific data |
| **Workspace dependencies** | Only depend on @ai-sdk/provider and @ai-sdk/provider-utils |
| **Composite TypeScript** | Project references for monorepo dependency tracking |
| **Dual exports** | Both CJS and ESM outputs via tsup |

This structure makes it easy to:
1. Add new model types by creating new model factory methods
2. Support multiple API endpoints consistently
3. Share configuration and headers
4. Extend with provider-specific functionality
5. Maintain type safety across the monorepo

